  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to examine three different ways to control pain after hip
      replacement:

        1. One time injection of ropivacaine before wound closure

        2. One time injection of ropivacaine before wound closure plus slow release of ropivacaine
           via catheter for 48 hours

        3. Standard practice of patient controlled pump
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
